07/07/2005
PALE, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- NATO troops reportedly detained Sasa Karadzic, son of the wartime Republika Srpska leader Radovan Karadzic, in Pale Thursday (7 July) morning.
Local media reports said the younger Karadzic was flown away by helicopter.
EUFOR spokesman Frank Cockburn was quoted as saying he would comment after the operation was completed.
(RTRS, Srna, NTV Hayat, Tanjug, RTS - 07/07/05)
